ðŸ”¹ Features

User-Based Collaborative Filtering: Suggests books based on similar user preferences.

K-Means Clustering: Groups users with similar reading patterns.

Hybrid Recommendation: Combines clustering and collaborative filtering for better personalization.

Interactive: Users can input their favorite books and get tailored suggestions.

Scalable: Works efficiently with large datasets of books and user ratings.

ðŸ›  Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/801NITHU2213/Hybrid-Book-Recommendation-System-Python-K-Means-Collaborative-Filtering.git


Navigate to the project directory:

cd Hybrid-Book-Recommendation-System-Python-K-Means-Collaborative-Filtering


Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt


Dependencies include:

pandas

numpy

scikit-learn

matplotlib

âš¡ Usage

Open the notebook Untitled10.ipynb in Jupyter Notebook or Google Colab.

Ensure books.csv and ratings.csv are in the same directory.

Run the notebook cells step by step.

Input your favorite books to get personalized recommendations.
